<TITLE> BOA allocates training fund to federations </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 19 (bdnews24.com)  The Bangladesh Olympic Association (BOA) Wednesday allocated Tk 12.34 lakh to seven federations to run the camps for the upcoming 2nd Indo-Bangladesh Bangla Games. The Bangladesh Football Federation has got the highest amount of Tk 3,20,500 for under-19 boys and girls booters, followed by the Bangladesh Swimming Federation getting Tk 2,18,750, according to a BOA press release. Apart from football and swimming, other federations which also got the allocations are the Bangladesh Basketball Federation (Tk 1,37,750), the Bangladesh Volleyball Federation (Tk 1,15,250), National Shooting Federation (Tk 1,67,000), Bangladesh Kabaddi Federation (Tk 1,37,750) and Bangladesh Kho Kho Federation (Tk 1,37,750). About 308 athletes from eight disciplines for the Indo-Bangla Games started training from September 10 at different venues under their respective federations. The BOA is supervising the camps and conducting only the athletics camp as there is a stay order of the High Court over the new ad-hoc committee of the Bangladesh Amateur Athletic Federation. 
